   The company also said it entered into "a definitive
agreement" for the sale of substantially all its HQ Office
Supplies Warehouse retail stores in Southern California to
Staples Inc., and "an agreement in principle" to sell its
stores in Northern California and Las Vegas, Nev., to BizMart
Inc.
   HQ Office Supplies said its "repositioning" is due in part
to its inability to close financing on a $40 million private
preferred equity placement during the fall of 1990. In
addition, the company said it was hurt earlier this year by
delays on the part of its underwriter.
