PETROLEUM (PET)
</IN>
<LP>
   The California Public Utilities Commission approved
Pacific Gas &amp; Electric Co.'s plan to expand a 900-mile
natural gas pipeline from British Columbia in Canada to
California.
   The $1.2 billion project still requires approval by the
Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, which has indicated it
will make a decision shortly. The California regulatory
approval covers only the 415 miles of pipeline within the
state, and not the parts through Idaho, Washington and
Oregon. The California commission's approval is conditioned
