MAJOR MONEY CENTER BANKS (BAN)
BANKS (BNK)
</IN>
<LP>
   Barclays Bank PLC, the largest commercial bank in Britain,
said it completed the acquisition of a 51% stake in
L'Europeenne de Banque, the banking arm of Credit Commercial
de France of France.
   The bank, which confirmed Dec. 13 that it had made a
conditional offer to CCF for the unit, founded in 1817, also
said it signed a letter of intent to acquire the balance of
the French institution's interest by early 1991. It said the
total value of the transaction, once completed, is 1.5
billion French francs ($288.5 million).
